Joi Lansing https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joi_Lansing 0 Joi Lansing (born Joy Rae Brown, April 6, 1929 – August 7, 1972) was an American model, film and television actress, and nightclub singer. She was noted for her pin-up photos and roles in B-movies, as well as a prominent role in the famous opening "tracking shot" in Orson Welles' crime drama Touch of Evil.
